{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_15366",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "4018f02d962882993d4f7d348ab739fed8bd8e3b",
  "pr_number": 15366,
  "issue_number": 15365,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Document preview and image endpoints return HTTP 500 when storage blob is missing",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### RAGFlow workspace code commit ID\n\n7fc909acc9961e57997e07ebbd0c6bd74cf8665d\n\n### RAGFlow image version\n\n7fc909acc\n\n### Other environment information\n\n```Markdown\n- OS type: Linux\n- Others: Reproducible from source on `main` in `api/apps/restful_apis/document_api.py` (`get_document_image`, preview `get`). Self-hosted / Docker deployments using current `main`.\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n\nWhen object storage returns no bytes, `get_document_image()` and document preview call `make_response(data)` with `data=None`. Quart raises:\n\n```text\nTypeError: The response value returned by the view function cannot be None\n```\n\nThe client receives HTTP **500** instead of a structured 4xx error.\n\n**Images** \u2014 no check after storage fetch:\n\n```python\ndata = await thread_pool_exec(settings.STORAGE_IMPL.get, bkt, nm)\nresponse = await make_response(data)\n```\n\n**Preview** (`GET /api/v1/documents/<doc_id>/preview`) \u2014 same pattern:\n\n```python\ndata = await thread_pool_exec(settings.STORAGE_IMPL.get, b, n)\nresponse = await make_response(data)\n```\n\n(`document_api.py` approx. lines 1671\u20131674 and 1877\u20131879 on `main`.)\n\n**Artifact** on the same file already guards correctly:\n\n```python\nif not data:\n    return get_data_error_result(message=\"Artifact not found.\")\n```\n\nDocument REST download also returns JSON when empty:\n\n```python\nif not file_stream:\n    return construct_json_result(message=\"This file is empty.\", code=RetCode.DATA_ERROR)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf `not data` after `STORAGE_IMPL.get`, return `get_data_error_result(...)` (e.g. `\"Image not found.\"` / `\"File is empty.\"`) with an appropriate 4xx code \u2014 never call `make_response(None)`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```Markdown\n**Preview**\n\n1. Ensure a document row exists in the DB but delete its object from MinIO/S3 (or use a stale storage address).\n2. Request preview with valid auth:\n\n\ncurl -sS -H \"Authorization: Bearer <api_key>\" \\\n  \"http://<host>/api/v1/documents/<doc_id>/preview\"\n\n\n3. Observe HTTP 500 and `TypeError` in server logs.\n4. Expected: structured 4xx JSON error (similar to artifact download or document REST download when storage is empty).\n\n**Images**\n\n1. Request `GET /api/v1/documents/images/<kb_id>-<object_key>` where the object does not exist in storage (valid ID format, missing blob).\n2. Observe HTTP 500 instead of `\"Image not found.\"` (4xx JSON).\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n- Affected code: `api/apps/restful_apis/document_api.py` \u2014 `get_document_image()` and preview `get()`.\n- Related but distinct: [#15115](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/15115) (mis-parsed image ID can lead to empty blob \u2014 one repro path \u2014 but empty-blob guard is still needed for deleted objects and invalid keys), [#15267](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/15267) (preview access control).\n- Suggested fix: add `if not data: return get_data_error_result(...)` before `make_response()` in both handlers, mirroring `get_artifact()`.\n- Same bug class as missing-blob handling on `GET /api/v1/files/<file_id>` (see separate report).",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-03T03:33:03.000Z",
